@endpoint POST /v13/deployments
@desc Create a new deployment
@required {name: str # A string with the project name used in the deployment URL}
@optional {forceNew: any(0/1) # Forces a new deployment even if there is a previous similar deployment, skipAutoDetectionConfirmation: any(0/1) # Allows to skip framework detection so the API would not fail to ask for confirmation, teamId: str # The Team identifier or slug to perform the request on behalf of., $schema: str # Ignored. Can be set to get completions, validations and documentation in some editors., alias: [str] # Aliases that will get assigned when the deployment is `READY` and the target is `production`. The client needs to make a `GET` request to its API to ensure the assignment, build: map # An object containing another object with information to be passed to the Build Process, buildCommand: str # The build command for this project. When `null` is used this value will be automatically detected, builds: [map] # A list of build descriptions whose src references valid source files., cleanUrls: bool # When set to `true`, all HTML files and Serverless Functions will have their extension removed. When visiting a path that ends with the extension, a 308 response will redirect the client to the extensionless path., crons: [map] # An array of cron jobs that should be created for production Deployments., deploymentId: str # An deployment id for an existing deployment to redeploy, devCommand: str # The dev command for this project. When `null` is used this value will be automatically detected, env: map # An object containing the deployment's environment variable names and values. Secrets can be referenced by prefixing the value with `@`, files: [any] # A list of objects with the files to be deployed, framework: str(None/blitzjs/nextjs/gatsby/remix/astro/hexo/eleventy/docusaurus-2/docusaurus/preact/solidstart/dojo/ember/vue/scully/ionic-angular/angular/polymer/svelte/sveltekit/sveltekit-1/ionic-react/create-react-app/gridsome/umijs/sapper/saber/stencil/nuxtjs/redwoodjs/hugo/jekyll/brunch/middleman/zola/hydrogen/vite/vitepress/vuepress/parcel/sanity) # The framework that is being used for this project. When `null` is used no framework is selected, functions: map # An object describing custom options for your Serverless Functions. Each key must be glob pattern that matches the paths of the Serverless Functions you would like to customize (like `api/*.js` or `api/test.js`)., git: map, gitMetadata: map # Populates initial git metadata for different git providers., gitSource: any # Defines the Git Repository source to be deployed. This property can not be used in combination with `files`., headers: [map] # A list of header definitions., ignoreCommand: str, installCommand: str # The install command for this project. When `null` is used this value will be automatically detected, meta: map # An object containing the deployment's metadata. Multiple key-value pairs can be attached to a deployment, monorepoManager: str # The monorepo manager that is being used for this deployment. When `null` is used no monorepo manager is selected, outputDirectory: str # The output directory of the project. When `null` is used this value will be automatically detected, project: str # The target project identifier in which the deployment will be created. When defined, this parameter overrides name, projectSettings: map # Project settings that will be applied to the deployment. It is required for the first deployment of a project and will be saved for any following deployments, public: bool # Whether a deployment's source and logs are available publicly, redirects: [map] # A list of redirect definitions., regions: [str] # An array of the regions the deployment's Serverless Functions should be deployed to, rewrites: [map] # A list of rewrite definitions., routes: [any] # A list of routes objects used to rewrite paths to point towards other internal or external paths, target: str(staging/production) # Either not defined, `staging`, or `production`. If `staging`, a staging alias in the format `<project>.<team>.now.sh` will be assigned. If `production`, any aliases defined in `alias` will be assigned, trailingSlash: bool # When `false`, visiting a path that ends with a forward slash will respond with a `308` status code and redirect to the path without the trailing slash., withLatestCommit: bool # When `true` and `deploymentId` is passed in, the sha from the previous deployment's `gitSource` is removed forcing the latest commit to be used.}
@returns(200) {alias: [str], aliasAssigned: bool, aliasAssignedAt: null?, aliasError: map?, aliasFinal: str?, aliasWarning: map?, automaticAliases: [str], bootedAt: num, build: map{env: [str]}, buildErrorAt: num, buildingAt: num, builds: [map], canceledAt: num, checksConclusion: str, checksState: str, createdAt: num, createdIn: str, creator: map{uid: str, username: str}, env: [str], errorCode: str, errorLink: str, errorMessage: str?, errorStep: str, functions: map?, gitRepo: null?, gitSource: any, id: str, inspectorUrl: str?, isInConcurrentBuildsQueue: bool, lambdas: [map], meta: map, monorepoManager: str?, name: str, ownerId: str, plan: str, previewCommentsEnabled: bool, projectId: str, public: bool, readyState: str, regions: [str], routes: [any]?, source: str, target: str?, team: map{id: str, name: str, slug: str}, type: str, url: str, userAliases: [str], version: num} # The successfully created deployment
@errors {400: One of the provided values in the request body is invalid.
